<p>Madagascar’s presidency warned of “an attempted illegal and forcible seizure of power” after members of the elite CAPSAT unit joined youth-led protests in Antananarivo, urged other troops to disobey orders, and refused to shoot at demonstrators [reuters.com#2][nytimes.com#1][france24.com#8]. The mutinous unit has claimed leadership of the military command and said it controls all armed forces, while the presidency condemned efforts to destabilize the country, called for protecting constitutional order, and encouraged dialogue to resolve the crisis [bbc.com#4][dw.com#3][aljazeera.com#6][reuters.com#2]. The protests began on September 25 over water and electricity shortages and have expanded to demands that President Andry Rajoelina step down, apologize for protester deaths, and dissolve the</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/saW2aO6qRbVY9mjei7aUSrEeic_UfkfGqt4AmSyEKz81nbPxceTpHvsUxMue1v9vwkDCRw3NRevRd3ijRThfDD6D8ikdiOL-DfrDVtraAJDKQAiZhkdQjyXrycrvQPizuRl_C9AdWDPMpsryk0JDr9optn7LaeJPMFyWUnM66w3KHxemsxKp_Vhq1mpiykP0_NdSMaMENkpjek6BLejXSE7Z9w' alt='Demonstrators cheer as members of a military unit arrive in Antananarivo.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Defecting unit: Troops from the elite CAPSAT unit—instrumental in Rajoelina’s 2009 takeover—urged soldiers to disobey orders and support protesters [reuters.com#2][nytimes.com#1].</li><li>Protest origins: The movement began over water and electricity shortages and drew inspiration from Gen Z-led protests in Kenya and Nepal [reuters.com#2].</li><li>Casualty figures: The UN reports at least 22 dead and 100 injured since September; the government disputes this, with Rajoelina saying 12 were killed [reuters.com#2].</li><li>Control claim: The mutinied unit asserted it had taken over the military command and all armed forces [bbc.com#4][dw.com#3][aljazeera.com#6][france24.com#8].</li><li>Sunday clashes: Three people were seen injured after shots near the CAPSAT barracks on Sunday, though other witnesses reported no ongoing clashes [reuters.com#2].</li></ul><blockquote>To stand together in defense of constitutional order and national sovereignty - Madagascar presidency</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Madagascar presidency: Condemned attempts to destabilize the country, urged defense of constitutional order, and encouraged dialogue. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/madagascar-presidency-warns-attempted-coup-without-offering-evidence-2025-10-12/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>CAPSAT soldiers: Called on security forces to disobey superiors and refuse to shoot at demonstrators; later claimed control of the armed forces. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd070pn4g07o'>BBC</a>)</li><li>Protesters: Demand Rajoelina step down, apologize for protester deaths, and dissolve the Senate and the electoral commission. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/madagascar-presidency-warns-attempted-coup-without-offering-evidence-2025-10-12/'>Reuters</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/11/world/africa/madagascar-protest-coup-fears.html'>Fears of a Coup Rise in Madagascar as Army Unit Joins Protesters</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/madagascar-presidency-warns-attempted-coup-without-offering-evidence-2025-10-12/'>Madagascar president warns of attempted coup after soldiers join protests</a> - reuters.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/madagascar-president-rajoelina-warns-of-attempted-coup/a-74323019'>Madagascar President Rajoelina warns of attempted coup</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd070pn4g07o'>Madagascar presidency says attempt to seize power under way</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/12/madagascar-s-president-says-attempt-to-seize-power-illegally-is-underway_6746345_4.html'>Madagascar&#x27;s president says &#x27;attempt to seize power illegally&#x27; is underway</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li